raw_data.title: Health IT Consultant
raw_data.description: Provides IT services in a health, research, or human service environment, drawing upon observed best practices and industry standards, with guidance. Able to provide specific Health IT services directly or provide review of technical solutions/implementations. Ability to provide specific knowledge of Custom off the Shelf (COTS) Health IT solutions or Government Off the Shelf (GOTS) Health IT solutions. Able to work as part of a team or with supervision.

raw_data.title: Health IT Systems Analyst
raw_data.description: Oversees the evaluation and redesign of business processes to enhance business functionality and efficiency and to facilitate large-scale Health IT change. Leads efforts to seek ways of applying new and existing Health IT technology to business processes, providing expertise on technical trends and external practices. Determines appropriate Health IT system life cycle techniques and methods for implementation. Communicates with other Health IT functional areas to apprise them of project status, inform senior management of progress, and brokers Health IT services with suppliers and vendors on behalf of customers.

raw_data.title: Health IT Analyst I
raw_data.description: Under direction, provides Health IT services, drawing upon observed best practices and industry standards. Applies domain specific experience with Health IT systems, methodologies, or technologies such as, but not limited to, automation, microservices, API, Cloud Management, databases/data warehouses, predictive analytics, containerization, custom reporting, or web applications, etc. Able to provide specific Health IT services directly or provide review of technical solutions/implementations. Ability to provide specific knowledge of Custom off the Shelf (COTS) Health IT solutions or Government Off the Shelf (GOTS) Health IT solutions.

raw_data.title: Health IT Analyst II
raw_data.description: In addition to being able to perform Health IT Program Analyst I duties, engages with internal and external stakeholders on health program or health system initiatives. Often works closely with more junior analysts. Capable of analyzing SAS extracts, providing health data, health systems, health policy, or Health IT expertise. Often participates in activities like creating user stories, working with design and/or development teams, participating in health system testing, or leading system training. Often participates in creating stakeholder participation strategies, reviewing data, creating reports, or system change requests, etc.

raw_data.title: Health IT Analyst III
raw_data.description: In addition to being able to perform Health IT Analyst II duties, capable of analyzing information, providing solutions, identifying and mitigating risks to health IT systems or programs as result of change Creates stakeholder participation strategies, reviews data, creates reports, or system change requests, etc. May ensure compliance with federal health mandates.

raw_data.title: Health IT Analyst IV
raw_data.description: In addition to being able to perform Health IT Analyst III duties is able to provide specific Health IT services directly or provide review of technical or programmatic solutions/implementations in response to federal health mandates or polices. Ability to provide specific knowledge of Custom off the Shelf (COTS) Health IT solutions or Government Off the Shelf (GOTS) Health IT solutions.  Often leads teams of analysts.

raw_data.title: Business Management Analyst I
raw_data.description: Gathers information and contributes to analysis regarding business/management items such as budget, risks, program status, etc.

raw_data.title: Business Management Analyst II
raw_data.description: Capable of performing functions of the Business Management Analyst I, and capable of providing independent analysis of specific business functions. Able to identify trends and provide recommendations for further analysis.

raw_data.title: Business Management Consultant I
raw_data.description: Able to provide policy, business process, or change management support related to a specific program/business functions. Applies knowledge in a specific program or business function to solve organizational problems, business/management challenges, or improve overall program/business operations. Able to oversee a team of analysts.

raw_data.title: Business Management Consultant II
raw_data.description: In addition to being able to perform Business Management Consultant I duties provides a range of business or management functions to support the identification of risk, risk management, change support, budget formulation, grant management.  Able to create discrete components of solutions for business or management problems.

raw_data.title: Change Management Analyst
raw_data.description: Able to provide communication, organizational, and or management strategies to facilitate change.  This may include application of best practices, organizational training, process redesign, etc.

raw_data.title: System Security Engineer
raw_data.description: Performs research, analysis and engineering of security features for system architectures. Engineers, maintains and improves solutions that meet security requirements. Analyzes general security related technical problems and provides technical support to resolve problems. Ensures that all information systems are functional and secure.

raw_data.title: System Security Architect
raw_data.description: Performs research, analysis, design, and development of security features for system architectures. Architects, designs, develops and implements solutions that meet security requirements. Analyzes general security related technical problems and provides technical support to resolve problems. Ensures that all information systems are functional and secure.

raw_data.title: Cybersecurity Project Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for the management, performance, and delivery of services for cybersecurity contracts and task orders. The Project Manager resolves project-related problems related to resourcing, budget and tasks.

raw_data.title: Cybersecurity Operations Specialist I
raw_data.description: Monitors information systems security operations. Provides Tier 1 incident response support. Develops and implements security standards and procedures. Evaluates security programs and coordinates tasks within. Applies knowledge and technical support to systems requiring specialized security features and procedures. Provides integration and implementation of the computer system security solutions.

raw_data.title: Cybersecurity Operations Specialist II
raw_data.description: Monitors information systems security operations. Provides Tier II incident response support. Develops and implements security standards and procedures. Evaluates security programs and coordinates tasks within. Applies knowledge and technical support to systems requiring specialized security features and procedures. Provides integration and implementation of the computer system security solutions.

raw_data.title: Cybersecurity Operations Specialist III
raw_data.description: Monitors information systems security operations. Provides Tier III incident response support. Develops and implements security standards and procedures. Evaluates security programs and coordinates tasks within. Applies knowledge and technical support to systems requiring specialized security features and procedures. Provides integration and implementation of the computer system security solutions.

raw_data.title: Cybersecurity Analyst I
raw_data.description: Responsible for applying cybersecurity and/or information assurance expertise and knowledge to either network and/or enterprise security. Performs analysis and applies “best practices” and security methodologies to systems. Expertise in one or more functional areas such as Risk/Vulnerability/Threat Assessments, Cloud Security, Security Operations, FW/IDS/IPS Configuration, Penetration Testing, Forensics, Threat Intelligence, Threat Hunting, etc. Interfaces with all necessary levels of management and staff. Keeps aware of state, local and federal trends, developments, standards, frameworks and regulations in the area of cybersecurity and informs the customer on impact to operations.

raw_data.title: Sr. Security Analyst
raw_data.description: Will monitor, evaluate, and maintain systems and procedures to safeguard internal information systems and databases. Researches, recommends, and implements changes to enhance systems security. Educates and communicates security requirements and procedures to all users and new employees. Identifies potential threats and responds to reported security incidents/violations. Determines cause of security violations and recommends corrective actions. Researches, recommends, and implements changes to procedures and systems to enhance systems security. Assists in the development of and conducts periodic system security tests. May also perform complex analyses on test results and prepares reports on this information for management.

raw_data.title: Security Analyst
raw_data.description: Performs day-to-day security risk assessment of IT infrastructure, including all systems, networks, and connectivity, and assists with application of security risk mitigation controls. Assesses and develops security solutions in the areas of security policy, security architecture, audits, and vulnerability assessments. Researches and documents new tools and techniques for current and future usage within IT systems and networks. Researches, analyzes, experiments, and applies different means of system compromise and penetration testing, and provides documentation for developments of potential security issues. Conducts computer and network forensic investigations where breaches of security are detected. Formulates and communicated highly technical and complex security concepts to technical and non-technical audiences in a clear and effective manner.

May construct workflow charts and diagrams, study system capabilities, and write specifications. May create end-user documentation (e.g., user guides, process flow charts, and training materials) and deliver training.

Establishes and implements standards for technical operations and compatibility between hardware and software, according to specifications and parameters.  May lead individuals assisting in the work.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: May act as the overall lead for a project or program.  Serves as the primary interface and point of contact with Government program authorities and representatives on technical and program/project issues. Supervises program/project operations by developing procedures, planning, and directing execution of the technical, programming, maintenance, and administrative support effort and monitoring and reporting progress. Manages acquisition and employment of program/project resources. Manages and controls financial and administrative aspects of the program/project with respect to contract requirements.

raw_data.title: Project Controller
raw_data.description: Assists in developing plans, including budgets and schedules, to meet contractual/project requirements for several major portions of a program.  Ensures compliance with internal procedures and government regulations. Monitors progress of program requirements.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Provides leadership over separate tasks, projects, or a portfolio of tasks.  May provide support to an organization on their strategy, priorities, change, or risk.  Strong planning, organization and communication skills are required.   May manage senior staff, project managers, or lines of business managers.  Expected to interact and engage with executive level staff.

raw_data.title: ERP Specialist I
raw_data.description: Supports the implementation, customization, enhancements, automation, or maintenance of large-scale ERP or COTS systems.  Provides requirement analysis, workflow support, may have expertise in a specific module or interface.

raw_data.title: ERP Specialist II
raw_data.description: Leads or is a large contributor to the implementation, customization, enhancements, automation, or maintenance of large-scale ERP or COTS systems.  Provides requirement analysis, workflow support, may have expertise in a specific module or interface.

raw_data.title: Computer Analyst
raw_data.description: Assists with the administration of applications, systems, and/or related environments to activities like, system administration, access management, patch management, performance turning, database administration, tools management, and or configuration management, or the deployment of automated tools.

raw_data.title: Developer
raw_data.description: Provides support to develop or maintain applications or systems or applicable environments.  May include all aspects of design, development and or testing support to include specific components of the application, system, or full stack development.
